        <h4>Master’s and undergraduate theses</h4>
        <p>Some Master’s and undergraduate programs offer students the option to deposit their theses or capstone projects in Academic Commons. Consult your program administrator or faculty advisor for specific program policies.</p>

        <h4>Alumni theses</h4>
        <p>Graduates of Columbia University and its affiliates can deposit their dissertation or thesis in Academic Commons with approval from the degree-granting program. Contact the administrator of your degree program to request permission to deposit.</p>

        <h4>Thesis embargoes</h4>
        <p>If your degree program requires or encourages you to deposit your thesis in Academic Commons, you may have the option of placing an embargo on your thesis. An embargo is a limited period of time during which your thesis is not publicly available. During the embargo period, descriptive information about the work is publicly accessible in Academic Commons and in CLIO, the Columbia Libraries catalog, but the thesis itself is not available. Embargo options vary by program and students should consult their degree program’s policies for more information.</p>

        <h4>Embargo changes</h4>
        <p>If you wish to make changes to the length of the embargo on your thesis in Academic Commons, contact the degree-program administrator with your request. If the request is approved, the program administrator will direct Academic Commons staff to change the embargo release date.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Columbia Graduate School of Arts and Sciences: contact the Dissertation Office at <a href="mailto:dissertations@columbia.edu">dissertations@columbia.edu</a> to request changes to an embargo.</li>
          <li>Graduates of all other doctoral, Master’s, and undergraduate programs: contact the appropriate degree-program administrator to request changes to an embargo.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Embargo changes in ProQuest</h4>
        <p>If you also deposited a thesis to ProQuest you must contact ProQuest directly to request changes to the availability of your work in the ProQuest dissertation and thesis database. Contact ProQuest at <a href="mailto:disspub@proquest.com">disspub@proquest.com</a>.</p>

        <h4>Other student works</h4>
        <p>If you are a student and want to deposit work in Academic Commons, you must have approval of a department or degree program. Contact us at <a href="mailto:ac@columbia.edu">ac@columbia.edu</a> to learn more.</p>

